  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb5 \u0baa\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Negotiations with Sri Lanka can be concluded as soon as possible - Managing Director of the International Monetary Fund",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "The International Monetary Fund has said that it wants to conclude the negotiations to rescue Sri Lanka from the economic crisis as soon as possible.",
        "He mentioned this while commenting to Tokyo's Nikkei Asia. He mentioned that we are deeply concerned about the interests of the people of Sri Lanka who are facing a severe shortage of fuel, food and other essential items while foreign exchange is completely exhausted.",
        "Frustrated citizens have turned their anger toward a government that has dimmed expectations of debt restructuring and ousted a previously strong-willed president, whose parliament elected Ranil Wickremesinghe to replace him on Wednesday.",
        "Now that we have a government, we can proceed with our negotiations, and our team will go there, the Managing Director of the International Monetary Fund, Kristalina Georgieva, said that since we have already taken the best technical measures, we are confident that the technical team can be found in Sri Lanka as soon as possible so that the negotiations on the project can be completed as soon as possible.",
        "Wickremesinghe is no stranger to the International Monetary Fund, having been involved in negotiations as a finance minister and six-time prime minister, but is seen as highly unpopular among the public.",
        "He also noted that the IMF will hold talks with any Sri Lankan administration as long as the next leader enjoys support and has the longevity to lead Sri Lanka."
      ],
